WEBVTT

00:26.494 --> 00:27.695
GEORGE (OFFSCREEN): Want
me to come pick you up?

00:27.728 --> 00:28.596
LILY (ON PHONE): OK.

00:28.629 --> 00:29.630
GEORGE (OFFSCREEN): OK.

00:29.663 --> 00:30.398
Oh, that's what they tell me.

00:30.431 --> 00:31.199
OK, all right.

00:31.232 --> 00:32.600
Bye.

00:32.633 --> 00:33.601
Hey, Merry.

00:33.634 --> 00:34.502
Hey.

00:34.535 --> 00:35.803
MERRY (ON PHONE): Hey.

00:35.836 --> 00:36.804
-Sure.

00:36.837 --> 00:38.472
Yeah, I'll come pick her up.

00:38.506 --> 00:40.274
This is the best protein
drink ever right here.

00:44.478 --> 00:47.681
Gotta stay lean and fit.

00:47.715 --> 00:52.686
Omega-3s, omega-6s, and a little
bit of saturated fat.

00:52.720 --> 00:54.588
But it's good fat.

00:54.622 --> 00:56.490
Ah, maybe I'll cut a mango up.

00:56.524 --> 00:57.491
Let's just try that one today.

00:57.525 --> 00:58.659
Oh, man, that's a raw--

00:58.692 --> 01:00.228
that's a pretty old mango.

01:00.261 --> 01:02.263
This is what it's like when
you're a bachelor.

01:02.296 --> 01:04.298
You have old, raw stuff.

01:07.568 --> 01:09.337
It-- it doesn't need
to go in there.

01:17.178 --> 01:19.147
Oh, I almost forgot--

01:19.180 --> 01:22.450
forgot my, uh, coffee.

01:22.483 --> 01:23.651
I've done that before.

01:27.621 --> 01:30.458
But we're about to go pick up
my daughter right now, which

01:30.491 --> 01:32.226
is great because Lily
lives close to me.

01:32.260 --> 01:33.494
And it's wonderful.

01:33.527 --> 01:35.229
But she lives with me half
the time or with

01:35.263 --> 01:36.230
mom half the time.

01:36.264 --> 01:38.366
We have a good relationship.

01:38.399 --> 01:39.667
Hey, sweetie.

01:39.700 --> 01:42.870
There you go.

01:42.903 --> 01:44.272
Lily, are you--

01:44.305 --> 01:46.307
are you already texting
this morning?

01:46.340 --> 01:47.608
Oh, my gosh.

01:47.641 --> 01:48.576
How many texts do you
think you do a day?

01:51.445 --> 01:52.413
-Oh, you don't do 1,000.

01:52.446 --> 01:54.348
But you do a lot, don't you?

01:54.382 --> 01:55.849
Are you-- a day?

01:55.883 --> 01:57.251
See you about 2:00.

01:59.687 --> 02:02.456
Are you excited about
coming today?

02:02.490 --> 02:03.524
Huh?

02:03.557 --> 02:04.425
It's going to be
fun, isn't it?

02:04.458 --> 02:05.626
What are we do today?

02:05.659 --> 02:08.229
Are we going to do two
fillings today?

02:08.262 --> 02:11.765
I think we are, aren't we?

02:11.799 --> 02:13.867
Can I ask-- can I ask
you another-- can

02:13.901 --> 02:15.736
I ask another question?

02:15.769 --> 02:16.870
Please?

02:16.904 --> 02:20.674
Just one more question,
just one.

02:20.708 --> 02:22.676
I'm not going to ask
two questions.

02:28.249 --> 02:29.617
Can I ask three questions?

02:29.650 --> 02:32.186
KID (OFFSCREEN): Yes.

02:32.220 --> 02:34.555
GEORGE (OFFSCREEN): Can I ask
you just like-- can I ask five

02:34.588 --> 02:36.957
questions or one?

02:36.990 --> 02:37.925
Five--

02:37.958 --> 02:38.959
all right.

02:38.992 --> 02:39.793
Question number five.

02:39.827 --> 02:40.561
You ready?

02:40.594 --> 02:42.463
[phone rings]

02:42.496 --> 02:43.797
-Dr. Hardy's office.

02:43.831 --> 02:45.533
This is Tina.

02:45.566 --> 02:48.536
-If you was another age-- if
you were another age, would

02:48.569 --> 02:50.538
you like to be seven or eight?

02:50.571 --> 02:52.273
If you-- could you--

02:52.306 --> 02:54.308
which would you like to--

02:54.342 --> 02:56.544
can I ask you another
question?

02:56.577 --> 03:00.748
-Dr. Hardy as a boss is just
like he is as a friend.

03:00.781 --> 03:04.385
I mean, we to him just
like he's one of us.

03:04.418 --> 03:07.221
We talk to him about anything.

03:07.255 --> 03:09.690
-Not long after George set up
his practice, we had some

03:09.723 --> 03:13.694
students who had major dental
work that needed to be done.

03:13.727 --> 03:18.299
And George, after one phone
call, took that on, basically

03:18.332 --> 03:21.602
transformed the lives of a
couple of kids by doing their

03:21.635 --> 03:23.337
dental work totally free.

03:23.371 --> 03:26.307
Didn't have to do that, but did
it because he know that's

03:26.340 --> 03:27.308
what those kids needed.

03:27.341 --> 03:28.642
And it's change their lives.

03:28.676 --> 03:30.578
-Which one do you like?

03:30.611 --> 03:32.513
Which one do you
like, sweetie?

03:32.546 --> 03:36.684
-George Hardy is the most
authentic, alive person.

03:36.717 --> 03:38.952
A lot of people, as they get
older, they get set in their

03:38.986 --> 03:40.788
ways, and they get bored
with their life.

03:40.821 --> 03:42.656
Or they just get settled.

03:42.690 --> 03:43.957
Somebody like George--
he's not settled.

03:43.991 --> 03:44.692
You know?

03:44.725 --> 03:45.826
He's alive.

03:45.859 --> 03:46.894
-Will you kill me
if I tell them?

03:46.927 --> 03:47.628
-No, tell them.

03:47.661 --> 03:49.397
Tell them.

03:49.430 --> 03:52.366
-The reason that the home town
folks love George is because

03:52.400 --> 03:56.370
George dresses up like a roller
blading tooth fairy in

03:56.404 --> 03:58.439
the Christmas parade
every year.

04:04.345 --> 04:05.479
-I'm--

04:05.513 --> 04:06.380
I'm trying to think
of somebody that

04:06.414 --> 04:07.915
might not like George.

04:07.948 --> 04:08.582
I can't think of one person who
doesn't like George Hardy.

04:11.519 --> 04:18.426
I mean if his ex-wife likes
him as much as I like him,

04:18.459 --> 04:20.994
then, you know, I think it'd be
pretty hard for anybody to

04:21.028 --> 04:22.763
not like George.

04:22.796 --> 04:26.400
-He has always been one of the
most fun people that I know.

04:26.434 --> 04:29.670
I don't think I've ever seen
George when he wasn't smiling.

04:29.703 --> 04:31.004
-Hey, Barbara.

04:31.038 --> 04:31.905
-Hey, George.

04:31.939 --> 04:32.873
How are you?

04:32.906 --> 04:33.574
-Good, how about you?

04:33.607 --> 04:34.442
-I'm fine.

04:34.475 --> 04:36.610
Good to see you too.

04:36.644 --> 04:39.547
He loves people, and he likes
the reaction that

04:39.580 --> 04:40.881
he gets from people.

04:40.914 --> 04:42.383
-How you been?

04:42.416 --> 04:44.518
You always answer the
phone so great here.

04:44.552 --> 04:45.519
I just--

04:45.553 --> 04:46.053
-Oh, thank you.

04:46.086 --> 04:47.588
Thank you.

04:47.621 --> 04:48.689
-Really, honestly, every
time I call down here.

04:48.722 --> 04:50.491
Hey, how you doing?

04:50.524 --> 04:54.795
-He is one of the-- the kindest
and finest people that

04:54.828 --> 04:58.599
I have ever seen in my life,
even though he's my son.

04:58.632 --> 05:01.001
He's just-- he's just
fun to be around.

05:05.606 --> 05:06.940
MICHAEL (OFFSCREEN): What did
you think of your son's

05:06.974 --> 05:10.010
performance in "Troll 2?"

05:10.043 --> 05:11.579
-Oh, my gosh.

05:11.612 --> 05:15.115
[laughs]

05:15.148 --> 05:16.717
Let's say, he's--

05:16.750 --> 05:17.918
he's not very grand.

05:21.789 --> 05:24.525
-So where's that damn mirror?

05:24.558 --> 05:26.694
-Well, I left in about the
middle of the movie.

05:26.727 --> 05:28.095
I just couldn't take
it anymore.

05:28.128 --> 05:30.431
And I thought, what
is he doing?

05:30.464 --> 05:32.700
-It's got to be your
imagination or a

05:32.733 --> 05:34.067
hallucination.

05:34.101 --> 05:36.404
Are you still smoking
dope, Holly?

05:36.437 --> 05:37.971
-I've known George for years.

05:38.005 --> 05:41.074
And he came in the store one
day, and I asked him.

05:41.108 --> 05:43.444
I said, you know, George, were
you ever in a movie?

05:43.477 --> 05:45.446
And he said, uh, yes.

05:45.479 --> 05:46.614
Why?

05:46.647 --> 05:48.048
And I said, well, I
think I saw it.

05:48.081 --> 05:51.852
I said, I saw this movie "Troll
2." And it was just

05:51.885 --> 05:54.922
crazy because nobody in the
community even knew that

05:54.955 --> 05:56.724
George was in a film.

05:56.757 --> 06:00.394
-We don't speak too much about
it, but he did make his movie

06:00.428 --> 06:02.563
about 17 years ago.

06:02.596 --> 06:04.932
We didn't know whether to tell
people about it or kind of

06:04.965 --> 06:07.000
keep it quiet.

06:07.034 --> 06:08.802
-I walked up to the counter,
and I said to the fella--

06:08.836 --> 06:11.705
I said, I'm here to pick up a
movie that you've got on hold

06:11.739 --> 06:15.976
called "Troll 2." And this guy
that's standing next to me at

06:16.009 --> 06:18.045
the counter-- he was getting
another movie too.

06:18.078 --> 06:20.414
And he looked at me, and
he said, oh, my gosh.

06:20.448 --> 06:22.483
He said, that's the worst
movie I've ever seen.

06:28.522 --> 06:32.860
[screams]

06:32.893 --> 06:34.862
-Wait till you get home
and watch the movie.

06:34.895 --> 06:37.030
And he was right.

06:37.064 --> 06:38.098
-It was so bad.

06:38.131 --> 06:40.133
And he was so--

06:40.167 --> 06:42.503
his accent and his acting--

06:42.536 --> 06:44.838
it was just so--

06:44.872 --> 06:47.207
just the strangest
thing to watch.

06:47.240 --> 06:49.042
-It was so not him.

06:49.076 --> 06:50.578
You know?

06:50.611 --> 06:52.813
Knowing the real person
in seeing him doing--

06:52.846 --> 06:54.715
using the word acting loosely.

06:54.748 --> 06:56.149
It was just hilarious.

06:56.183 --> 06:59.219
-Do you see this writing?

06:59.252 --> 07:01.121
Do you know what it means?

07:03.791 --> 07:04.958
Hospitality.

07:06.827 --> 07:08.729
And you can't piss
on hospitality.

07:08.762 --> 07:10.831
I won't allow it!

07:10.864 --> 07:12.966
-What are you going to
do to me, daddy?

07:13.000 --> 07:14.535
-Tightening my belt
by one loop so I

07:14.568 --> 07:15.703
don't feel hunger pains.

07:15.736 --> 07:16.904
MICHAEL (OFFSCREEN):
OK, pause it.

07:16.937 --> 07:18.171
Rewind.

07:18.205 --> 07:19.573
He's right there.

07:23.010 --> 07:25.879
That's me, Michael
Paul Stephenson.

07:25.913 --> 07:30.918
And 18 years ago, I got the lead
role in my first movie.

07:30.951 --> 07:32.185
-Nilbog.

07:32.219 --> 07:34.655
It's goblin spelled backwards!

07:34.688 --> 07:36.724
MICHAEL (OFFSCREEN): At that
time, the movie was titled

07:36.757 --> 07:39.660
"Goblin." It was directed by
Italian filmmaker Claudio

07:39.693 --> 07:44.131
Fragasso and written by his
wife, Rosella Drudi.

07:44.164 --> 07:47.200
We filmed the movie over the
course of three weeks in

07:47.234 --> 07:50.904
small-town Utah in the
summer of 1989.

07:50.938 --> 07:51.905
It was hard work.

07:51.939 --> 07:53.206
It was-- it was tough work.

07:53.240 --> 07:56.744
But it was a small price
to pay for stardom.

08:01.982 --> 08:05.919
See, as a child actor, this was
the big break that I was

08:05.953 --> 08:07.187
waiting for.

08:07.220 --> 08:08.789
I thought that I was
going to be famous.

08:08.822 --> 08:12.225
I couldn't wait to see my
movie on the big screen.

08:12.259 --> 08:17.665
But my movie never made
it to the big screen.

08:17.698 --> 08:21.702
In fact, the first time that
I saw my movie was one year

08:21.735 --> 08:24.572
later on Christmas morning.

08:24.605 --> 08:31.845
I unwrapped my last present to
reveal a VHS copy of my movie.

08:31.879 --> 08:34.147
I was so excited to see
this for the first

08:34.181 --> 08:35.683
time with my family.

08:35.716 --> 08:37.751
I grabbed the tape, and
I stuck it in the VCR.

08:37.784 --> 08:40.988
And then I pressed play.

08:41.020 --> 08:44.224
[screams]

08:44.256 --> 08:46.927
-90 minutes later, my childhood

08:46.960 --> 08:48.261
dreams went up in flames.

08:52.700 --> 08:55.736
I hated this movie.

08:55.769 --> 09:00.140
I ran from "Troll 2," and I
wanted nothing to do with it.

09:00.173 --> 09:04.277
But that was before I realized
that there was more to this

09:04.311 --> 09:07.615
movie than I understood.

09:07.648 --> 09:11.284
And this is my movie
about that movie.

09:14.121 --> 09:16.023
-Tightening my belt
by one loop so I

09:16.056 --> 09:17.691
don't feel hunger pains.

09:17.725 --> 09:19.793
And your sister and mother
will have to do likewise.

09:19.827 --> 09:22.095
-I was practicing dentistry
in Salt Lake

09:22.129 --> 09:23.631
City, Utah at the time.

09:23.664 --> 09:24.998
I think it was about 1989.

09:25.032 --> 09:28.068
And on a whim, I auditioned
for this movie.

09:28.101 --> 09:29.637
And I did a few--

09:29.670 --> 09:33.273
did dentistry about two or
three days or four days.

09:33.306 --> 09:35.709
And then I'd go back and shoot
and then go back and do

09:35.743 --> 09:36.877
dentistry and go
back and shoot.

09:36.910 --> 09:39.046
I remember doing that
a few times.

09:39.079 --> 09:43.851
The way I first found out that
the movie was released was by

09:43.884 --> 09:45.352
one of my patients.

09:45.385 --> 09:47.855
My patient goes, I seen you
in that movie, Dr. Hardy.

09:47.888 --> 09:48.722
I seen you in that movie.

09:48.756 --> 09:49.923
I go, what movie?

09:49.957 --> 09:51.859
And he goes, "Troll 2."
And I go, what?

09:51.892 --> 09:52.660
What is the name?

09:52.693 --> 09:54.161
What?

09:54.194 --> 09:56.830
Within a day or two, I got a
copy of "Troll 2" on VHS.

09:56.864 --> 09:59.266
And I remember taking that
thing and putting it and

09:59.299 --> 10:01.669
watching my first scene with
Margo on the couch.

10:01.702 --> 10:03.270
-I'm worried about Joshua.

10:03.303 --> 10:06.139
He's still seeing
Grandpa Seth.

10:06.173 --> 10:09.276
-When I was a kid, I had an
imaginary playmate too.

10:09.309 --> 10:11.211
-But it wasn't your
dead grandfather.

10:11.244 --> 10:12.312
-And I thought, oh, man.

10:12.345 --> 10:13.881
This is-- this is bad.

10:13.914 --> 10:15.415
This is really, really bad.

10:15.448 --> 10:16.884
-Michael?

10:16.917 --> 10:19.319
-Yeah?

10:19.352 --> 10:22.355
-Who are the goblins?

10:22.389 --> 10:24.424
-The goblins?

10:24.457 --> 10:26.860
Oh, when it first started
showing up on HBO and all

10:26.894 --> 10:28.862
that, people would call
me from all over

10:28.896 --> 10:30.097
the freaking place.

10:30.130 --> 10:31.398
George, you're on TV!

10:34.835 --> 10:35.769
I'd just go, I know.

10:35.803 --> 10:36.670
I know.

10:36.704 --> 10:38.371
I know I've been on it.

10:38.405 --> 10:40.407
Just stop watching
it right now.

10:40.440 --> 10:42.142
It gets worse.

10:42.175 --> 10:47.280
-I went on a mission for my
church, and I was in Spain.

10:47.314 --> 10:50.150
And all of a sudden, one
day I get this letter.

10:50.183 --> 10:53.821
And it says, your movie's out.

10:53.854 --> 10:54.722
And it's

10:54.755 --> 10:56.790
called "Troll 2." -Damn.

10:56.824 --> 10:58.225
There's no milk.

10:58.258 --> 11:00.160
There's no coffee.

11:00.193 --> 11:01.729
There's nothing.

11:01.762 --> 11:03.764
Guys, didn't anyone remember
to bring supplies?

11:03.797 --> 11:08.168
-And the first time that I saw
it, it was embarrassing.

11:08.201 --> 11:11.238
I've got to admit, it was
embarrassing because m acting

11:11.271 --> 11:13.006
was horrible.

11:13.040 --> 11:18.946
And I think I maybe hoped it
wouldn't be as bad as it was.

11:18.979 --> 11:20.413
But it was.

11:20.447 --> 11:25.485
(SINGING) I'd like to dance
with you, honey.

11:25.518 --> 11:28.989
I'd like to have romance.

11:29.022 --> 11:30.357
I was in a crappy movie.

11:30.390 --> 11:32.860
And I'm a crappy actor.

11:32.893 --> 11:34.995
And that's OK because it's
not my thing that I do.

11:35.028 --> 11:36.163
I do music.

11:36.196 --> 11:37.798
I don't need to run
from this film.

11:37.831 --> 11:42.770
But I can understand like Darren
and Connie and maybe

11:42.803 --> 11:46.940
some of the other ones that do
acting and are trying to make

11:46.974 --> 11:50.911
a career of acting, how they,
for a time, would try to just

11:50.944 --> 11:52.379
kind of brush this away.

11:52.412 --> 11:54.915
Who wants to put "Troll 2" on
their resume, you know?

11:54.948 --> 11:56.483
If someone pulls it out
and watches it, you're

11:56.516 --> 11:57.885
not getting the part.

11:57.918 --> 11:59.753
-Oh, I think I recognize you.

11:59.787 --> 12:01.889
Did you do a movie
about goblins

12:01.922 --> 12:03.290
or trolls or something?

12:03.323 --> 12:05.993
And there's that part of
you that wants to lie.

12:06.026 --> 12:06.960
It's not on my resume.

12:06.994 --> 12:08.528
You know?

12:08.561 --> 12:10.230
But then you're like, oh, I
shouldn't lie, because I he'll

12:10.263 --> 12:11.832
just look me up.

12:11.865 --> 12:14.334
And so you go, uh-huh, and
leaving knowing I'm not

12:14.367 --> 12:18.772
getting hired because of that.

12:18.806 --> 12:19.973
-[groans]

12:20.007 --> 12:21.141
-Release your instincts
in the bathroom!

12:21.174 --> 12:22.342
-Are you nuts?

12:22.375 --> 12:24.912
Are you trying to turn
me into a homo?

12:24.945 --> 12:26.446
-It wouldn't be too hard.

12:26.479 --> 12:29.416
If my father discovers you here,
he'd cut off your little

12:29.449 --> 12:30.550
nuts and eat them.

12:30.583 --> 12:33.020
He can't stand you.

12:33.053 --> 12:34.154
-I was horrible in it.

12:34.187 --> 12:36.256
And I knew I was
horrible in it.

12:36.289 --> 12:39.359
And I was, like, devastated as a
little kid who's just like--

12:39.392 --> 12:40.527
you know?

12:40.560 --> 12:42.462
Well, I was a pre-teen,
even worse.

12:42.495 --> 12:45.933
And I was just thinking,
oh, my gosh.

12:45.966 --> 12:49.236
I suck.

12:49.269 --> 12:50.971
I looked it up on--

12:51.004 --> 12:54.441
on IMDb, and it was like one of
those slow motion moments

12:54.474 --> 12:57.244
when you look down and you
see, like, the ratings.

12:57.277 --> 12:59.112
And it says, worst
movie ever made.

12:59.146 --> 13:01.281
And then I clicked
on Comments.

13:01.314 --> 13:04.551
That was a bad move.

13:04.584 --> 13:06.286
They're not just saying, that's
a horrible movie.

13:06.319 --> 13:11.091
They're saying, you are a
horrible actor in the movie.

13:11.124 --> 13:12.125
So it's not just the movie.

13:12.159 --> 13:14.094
It's you too.

13:14.127 --> 13:17.330
So it is personal.

13:17.364 --> 13:22.169
From the moment I saw it the
first time on HBO, from that

13:22.202 --> 13:25.906
very moment, I was like, oh,
I just want it to go away.

13:25.939 --> 13:27.607
I just want it to go away.

13:31.444 --> 13:33.046
CHRIS (OFFSCREEN): We can do
Holly's scene with the

13:33.080 --> 13:34.915
boyfriend coming
in the window.

13:34.948 --> 13:37.450
-I don't know that one.

13:37.484 --> 13:38.886
Are you Holly?

13:38.919 --> 13:40.287
-Sure.

13:40.320 --> 13:41.521
-I could be Holly.

13:41.554 --> 13:42.923
-[groans]

13:42.956 --> 13:45.292
-Release your instincts
in the bathroom!

13:45.325 --> 13:46.860
-Are you trying to turn
me into a homo?

