[music playing]

40:36.535 --> 40:38.470
[music playing]

41:17.876 --> 41:20.812
-Oh, boy.

41:20.846 --> 41:23.982
What attention, what suspense.

41:34.225 --> 41:35.927
-It's Claudio.

41:35.961 --> 41:39.230
Scott, I want to
introduce you.

41:39.264 --> 41:40.065
Scott, Claudio.

41:40.098 --> 41:40.932
-How are you?

41:40.966 --> 41:41.533
Nice to meet you.

41:41.567 --> 41:42.067
-Good.

41:42.100 --> 41:42.901
How are you?

41:42.934 --> 41:43.669
-Fine.

41:43.702 --> 41:44.636
-It's an honor.

41:44.670 --> 41:46.772
I'm a huge fan, huge fan.

41:46.805 --> 41:49.107
I saw this movie
when I was 15.

41:49.140 --> 41:50.075
-No.

41:50.108 --> 41:51.209
-Yeah.

41:51.242 --> 41:52.844
Now, um, I produce
horror movies.

41:52.878 --> 41:56.915
So it's amazing.

41:56.948 --> 41:59.250
-Yes.

41:59.284 --> 42:00.819
-Yes, absolutely.

42:00.852 --> 42:02.187
-So good to see you again.

42:02.220 --> 42:02.954
-I remember.

42:02.988 --> 42:03.822
-Oh, of course.

42:03.855 --> 42:05.223
Of course.

42:05.256 --> 42:07.192
Yes, you yelled at me a lot.

42:07.225 --> 42:08.193
-Oh, Chris.

42:08.226 --> 42:09.595
-Do you remember me?

42:13.765 --> 42:14.700
-So we're all here.

42:14.733 --> 42:16.101
It's pretty great.

42:16.134 --> 42:18.103
-In LA, yeah?

42:18.136 --> 42:20.939
-Yeah, right here
in Los Angeles.

42:20.972 --> 42:21.907
-That's it, yeah.

42:21.940 --> 42:22.908
You're right in it.

42:22.941 --> 42:24.109
You're right here.

42:28.146 --> 42:30.782
GEORGE (OFFSCREEN): This is
pretty good, pretty good.

42:30.816 --> 42:31.850
-Hello, how are you?

42:31.883 --> 42:32.618
Fine.

42:32.651 --> 42:33.785
-How you doing?

42:33.819 --> 42:35.687
-Have you seen this
movie before?

42:35.721 --> 42:36.121
-Yeah.

42:36.154 --> 42:37.088
Yeah.

42:37.122 --> 42:37.856
-What you think about it?

42:37.889 --> 42:38.857
-What was that?

42:38.890 --> 42:40.225
-What do you think about it?

42:40.258 --> 42:41.793
-Oh, we have a great time
watching this movie.

42:41.827 --> 42:43.061
Oh, yeah.

42:43.094 --> 42:43.829
-Ciao.

42:43.862 --> 42:45.631
Bye, bye.

42:45.664 --> 42:47.365
-"Troll 2." Yeah.

42:47.398 --> 42:48.767
-Did you see the movie?

42:48.800 --> 42:49.868
-Yeah, it was awesome.

42:49.901 --> 42:51.136
-What do you think about it?

42:51.169 --> 42:52.070
MALE SPEAKER (OFFSCREEN):
It's amazing.

42:52.103 --> 42:53.071
-It's amazing?

42:53.104 --> 42:54.072
-It's a miracle.

42:54.105 --> 42:55.641
I love it. "Troll 2." Woo!

43:15.393 --> 43:19.030
-Grandpa Seth has been gone for
more than six months now.

43:19.064 --> 43:21.900
You were at the funeral,
and I know it was very

43:21.933 --> 43:23.301
difficult for you.

43:23.334 --> 43:26.738
It was also very difficult
for your father and for

43:26.772 --> 43:28.707
Holly and for me--

43:28.740 --> 43:30.642
[laughter]

44:10.448 --> 44:14.352
-Every single bad movie out
there wants to be this film.

44:14.385 --> 44:18.456
It wants to be "Troll 2." Most
bad movies only have, like,

44:18.489 --> 44:21.693
two redeeming qualities or a
couple of scenes you share

44:21.727 --> 44:22.961
with your friends.

44:22.994 --> 44:25.296
The thing with "Troll
2," it delivers

44:25.330 --> 44:27.198
through the entire film.

44:27.232 --> 44:28.867
[laughter]

44:28.900 --> 44:34.205
-Um, we have about 90%, I
believe, of the cast here.

44:34.239 --> 44:36.141
[applause]

44:39.110 --> 44:40.445
-We have the director.

44:40.478 --> 44:42.380
[cheering]

